content:
Manage Secondary Language Translations

Einstein Bots is available in Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience. Setup for Einstein Bots is available in Lightning Experience.

Available in: Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions

USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED
To build and manage Einstein Bots:
Customize Application
OR
Modify Metadata
OR
Manage Bots

Einstein Bots uses Translation Workbench to store translations. Turn on Translation Workbench, set up secondary languages, and define translator users in Translation Workbench.

Users must have the Manage Translation permission or be assigned as a translator for a specific language in Translation Workbench to edit translations.

To edit bot translations:
In the Bot Builder, click Dialogs.
Select the dialog you want to translate, and then click the Dialog Translations tab.
From the language dropdown, select the language that you want to manage translations for.
The Translations section displays the selected languageâ€™s dialog step text.

To quickly add translations, select the dialog steps that you want to translate, and then click Translate Selected (beta). Or, to add translations manually, click  for the text that you want to add or edit.
